main event: On 8 February 1965, witnesses observed an unidentified flying object in Liberty, Ohio.
interesting points: Two witnesses, a husband and wife, reported seeing a glowing, circular object moving at high speed,The object was estimated to be approximately 50 feet in diameter and was observed for about 30 seconds before disappearing,The husband took two photographs of the object during the sighting,Investigators found the witnesses credible and the photographs appeared to be genuine,The investigation concluded that the object was classified as UNIDENTIFIED.
witness description: husband and wife driving in a vehicle
